outside the range of the matrix @code{m}, and the error is trapped by
the range-checking code in @code{gsl_matrix_get}.

@example
m_(0,0) = 0.23
m_(0,1) = 1.23
m_(0,2) = 2.23
m_(1,0) = 100.23
m_(1,1) = 101.23
m_(1,2) = 102.23
